content.content:
{
  "id": "D12",
  "question": "What is the rejection shape when animate() is called while Animator is paused (no session launched)?",
  "context": "animate() currently returns an AnimateHandle synchronously and the caller awaits `result`. Pre-check rejection produces no SessionDoc — so the rejection must travel on the handle, not on a persisted session. Options below cascade from 'minimal change' to 'biggest'.",
  "options": {
    "rejected-result": "AnimateHandle.result resolves with a synthesized SessionResult that has status `'rate-limited'` (per D6) and terminationReason payload, but no SessionDoc is written. Caller pattern-matches on status exactly as if the session had launched and rate-limited.",
    "throw-typed": "animate() throws `AnimatorPausedError` synchronously when paused. Handle is never returned. Existing try-catch pattern works but callers don't get a handle.",
    "new-handle-field": "AnimateHandle gains a `dispatch` discriminator: `'accepted' | { rejected: 'rate-limited', pausedUntil, reason }`. Pre-check returns a handle with `dispatch === 'rejected'` and empty chunks/result."
  },
  "recommendation": "rejected-result",
  "rationale": "`rejected-result` shares a single rejection shape with the 'in-flight session terminated rate-limited' case (same enum value, same `terminationReason` detail). One code path on consumers. `throw-typed` diverges from every other Animator failure mode (which resolves the promise, not throws). `new-handle-field` is shape churn for a one-off case.",
  "selected": "rejected-result",
  "patron": {
    "verdict": "confirm",
    "selection": "rejected-result",
    "confidence": "high",
    "rationale": "#4 fires cleanly — unified single-pass rejection shape shared with the in-flight-terminated case; throw-typed and new-handle-field both diverge consumer code paths."
  }
}
{
  "id": "D13",
  "question": "When in the animate() lifecycle does the pre-check happen?",
  "context": "animate() today: resolveProvider → resolveModel → generate id → buildProviderConfig → provider.launch(). Pre-check needs to happen before whatever the caller would observe as a launched session.",
  "options": {
    "top-of-animate": "Check status before generating any ids or calling the provider. No session id is issued; no session is recorded.",
    "after-init-before-launch": "Issue session id, run init, then check status just before provider.launch. A pending SessionDoc may or may not be written depending on ordering.",
    "per-provider": "Pre-check inside each provider's launch() — the Animator passes status through and providers decide whether to proceed."
  },
  "recommendation": "top-of-animate",
  "rationale": "Three Defaults: fail fast. Pre-check before id generation means no SessionDoc is ever written for a rejected call — no orphan pending records, no reconciler noise. Keeps the pre-check semantically identical whether the provider is attached or detached.",
  "selected": "top-of-animate",
  "patron": {
    "verdict": "confirm",
    "selection": "top-of-animate",
    "confidence": "high",
    "rationale": "#2 fires cleanly — fail fast before any id or SessionDoc is issued; later gates allow partial work to leak as orphan pending records."
  }
}
{
  "id": "D15",
  "question": "What does crawl() return when the gate suppresses both tryRun and trySpawn?",
  "context": "CrawlResult today has a large tagged union; `null` means no work available. A new 'paused' action variant could advertise the gate to callers (e.g. tests, UI).",
  "options": {
    "return-null": "Same as today — when nothing happened, return null. The crawl-continual loop idles normally.",
    "new-action-gated-by-pause": "Return a new `CrawlResult` variant like `{ action: 'gated-by-pause', pausedUntil }` so tests and observability can assert the gate fired."
  },
  "recommendation": "return-null",
  "rationale": "No existing caller branches on a 'we chose not to dispatch' result. Adding a new action variant ripples through CrawlResult union, tests, and logs without load-bearing use. Pause observability lives on the Animator status book (CDC stream) — not the scheduler tick output.",
  "selected": "return-null",
  "patron": {
    "verdict": "confirm",
    "selection": "return-null",
    "confidence": "high",
    "rationale": "#18 fires cleanly — a new CrawlResult variant has no consumer branching on it; pause observability lives on the Animator status CDC stream, not the scheduler tick output."
  }
}
{
  "id": "D18",
  "question": "How does Parlour surface the rate-limited rejection to its callers?",
  "context": "Parlour's takeTurn() returns `TurnResult = { sessionResult, turnNumber, conversationActive }`. On rate-limit, the SessionResult (per D6 and D12) carries `status: 'rate-limited'` and a `terminationReason`. Callers (nsg consult, nsg convene, parlour web UI) need to present the condition.",
