  "id": "c-mocdm7of-86ec1e810224",
  "goal": "Rate-limit-aware scheduling: detect when the anima provider is rate-limited (token exhaustion), pause dispatch, and auto-resume when the window reopens. Open sub-questions: (a) detection mechanism — reactive (wait for an engine to fail, enter 'resource exhausted' mode, probe periodically) vs proactive (token-usage heartbeat via cheap Haiku prompt, OAuth usage endpoint if one exists, UI-scraping via Playwright, etc.); (b) state scope — per-engine 'stuck with reason=no-tokens' vs Spider-level 'scheduler paused until tokens available' (guild-wide). Vocabulary: Coinmaster owns token tracking (Purse = per-commission budget); Sentinel is the Reckoner's reserved term for a scoped watcher that emits a Pulse through the Lattice when its condition fires — 'Purse balance exhausted' is one of the explicit example Sentinel conditions in the vocabulary tome.",
  "status": "concluded",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-24T03:54:11.679Z",
  "parentId": "c-mo1mq8ry-c8cf4810db6c",
  "createdSessionId": "f1f81a7b-e7fd-46b8-b70e-eebffb6beb9e",
  "conclusion": "Design resolved and dispatched as commission w-mocei999-ffc6a8c4972c, landed as sealed commit 1a9f038. Final shape: Animator owns rate-limit state via single-row status book in Stacks; detection is reactive A5 (parse provider failure signature) + A1 back-off (15m initial / 1hr cap / 2× factor, configurable as animator.rateLimitBackoff); both Spider-state (paused gate) and engine-state (stuck-with-reason as historical marker) — the hybrid shape. Haiku heartbeat rejected (model-asymmetry on Claude Max); API usage polling rejected (no endpoint on Max subscription); UI scraping deferred. In-flight sessions run to natural completion; pauseReason is extensible for future operator-pause. Observation-lift produced 10 children for backlog review.",
